[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We have a new free and open-source AI that can edit any videos just with a text prompt. And this is pretty good. For example, let\'s say we have this video. Well, we can replace her top with a green one with a ruffled neckline. And here\'s what we get. Or here\'s another'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'example where we can add a faint aurora in the sky. And here\'s what we get. You can easily insert objects in the video as well. So, let\'s add a vintage street lamp in the background. And here\'s your result. How cool is that? You can also'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'change anime into a realistic video like this. So, this AI is called Ditto and this is actually by Ant Groupoup, which is another branch by Alibaba, which also'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'created the best open-source video model out there called Juan. Anyways, this Ditto is based off of Juan, but it expands it further in that it allows you to edit videos just with a text prompt. So, in this video, I\'m going to go over'

[00:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'some examples and step by step how you can install this on your computer. so you can run it for free and unlimited times offline. First, let\'s start with some of their official demos. With Ditto, you can take an existing video or'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'act something out yourself and then just with the prompt, you can change the character or the background to whatever you want. So, for example, you can turn this into a dark mystical sorceress with glowing green eyes and here\'s what you'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'get. It\'s just so easy to manipulate a video now. Or here\'s another example where if this is your original video, well, you can prompt it with this and here is what you get. Or here\'s another cool example. If this is your original'

[01:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video and prompt, here\'s the result. The quality is also not bad. Here\'s another example. We can turn this person into something like this. However, notice that it\'s not that good with'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'expressions. So, in the original video, she\'s kind of talking and moving her eyes a bit, but in the output video, these expressions are not translated. In fact, if you want to transfer facial expressions, it\'s best to actually use'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'another tool called one animate, which is really useful. If you\'re interested in learning more, see this video for a full installation tutorial. You can also easily add objects into any video just with a prompt. So, for example, if this'

[02:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
