[10:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'would upload your video to edit. Notice that here is where you can force the frames per second. The default is 24 frames per second. And here\'s basically where you set the length of your output'

[10:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video. So 73 frames divided by 24 frames is roughly 3 seconds. If your uploaded video is longer than 3 seconds, but you only set it to 3 seconds, it\'s going to truncate it at 3 seconds. And then'

[10:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'afterwards, your video is fed into here. And here is where you can specify the width and the height of your final video. So if your video is in a different aspect ratio, for example, if it\'s a vertical video, remember to'

[10:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'actually change the width and the height here. And then here is where you can choose how you want to actually resize the video if these are in different dimensions compared to your original video. So you can either crop it or'

[10:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'stretch it etc. And then finally your video will be fed into one vase which I covered on my channel before. This is another really useful tool to transfer the movements of a character onto a new'

[11:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video. In fact, if you want to learn more about one vase, check out these two videos where I go over how to install and use it. Anyways, back to here. After plugging it through vase to basically apply the movements, it then gets'

[11:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'transferred over to this one video sampler to generate the video. Now, here are a few more settings that you need to be aware of. First of all, the step count is basically how many well steps the AI model goes through before'

[11:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'generating your final video. Now, usually one takes around 20 to 30 steps, but because we have this cosvid lower lora enabled, we can reduce the step count to four to make it generate a lot'

[11:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'faster. And then for CFG, this is basically how literally you want the AI to follow your prompt. So, a higher CFG number would follow your prompt more literally, whereas a lower CFG value'

[12:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'would introduce more creativity and variance to your generation. And then seed is basically like the starting image of random noise. Basically, if you keep all the settings the same and you use the same seed, you\'re going to'

[12:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'generate the exact same video as before. If you set it to a different seed, but you keep the rest of the settings the same, it\'s going to generate a slightly different video. So, usually I just set the seed to randomize. And then here is theuler or basically the algorithm used'

[12:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to generate the video. Feel free to play around with all of these, but I\'m just going to leave it at the default of uniC. And then the rest of the settings we can just leave it as is. And that\'s pretty much it. So let\'s start by'

